1- Create Java Project

2- Convert Project to Maven Project

3- Get dependicies from Maven Repo

####################

<!-- https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/org.seleniumhq.selenium/selenium-java -->
<dependencies>
<dependency>
    <groupId>org.seleniumhq.selenium</groupId>
    <artifactId>selenium-java</artifactId>
    <version>4.3.0</version>
</dependency>
</dependencies>


#####################

4- add the above code into POM file, just before <build> tag and after <version> tag
this will download all selenium jar files . save the file. you should see a new folder Maven Dependencies


5- selenium web drivers for chorem, firefox, safari is also there in Maven.
Copy them to POM file and save it

6- Add TestNG dependency from Maven as well

7- Chrome driver indirilmesi ve path girilmesi
8- driver.getTitle(), driver.close(), driver.getCurrentUrl(), driver.quit(), driver.get(URL)


######## Locators ############

9- locate by ID, by Xpath, by CSS
10- driver.findElement(By.id("username"))
11. driver.findElement(By.id("username")).sendKeys("mete");
12. css selector tagname.attribute

13. implicit wait : 









